===Etymology===
After {{w|lang=en|Marco Polo}} (1254–1324), Venetian merchant, whose travels were documented in a book that introduced Europeans to Central Asia and China.  The {{der|en|it|-}} name is from {{der|en|la|Marcus}} + {{m|la|Paulus}}.

